				What can I say? We all know how terrible Hags are, except for the mage in the previous post who will soon find out about these, pray that you don't fella. Anyway my group beat one the other day: Full Group: Myself 24 enc, 26 SK, 24 Cleric, 24 War, 22 and 25 rangers. We heard the usual &quot; Train to Zone... blah blah blah&quot; we see the train, D werebats, CG's and we decide to go try and clear it. We and some other ppl do, then a Hag comes up. OH BOY, so some of my group zone, 3 of em, then one ranger, the cleric and myself stay. She blasts me so my pet is meleeing with here, and I have alacrity on the ranger. So he is chipping away at her hp along with the pet, while cleric heals him and myself. In the  mean time, I cast tashani and repeatedly cast color shift to stun her so she cann't cast, she resisted a few times, but couldn't get off any more spells really, except for one AoE, big woop, pet dies and it is us 3, she gets to 30% hp and the cleric starts DDing as well as myself, so we kill her. Yeah, woohoo. Anyway try to stun her or bash or something, and only do this at that level close to the zone. Luckily she didn't manage to kill the cleric. ^_^
				</font>
